name: Jay Bhattacharya
summary: Former President Donald Trump has nominated Jay Bhattacharya, a prominent critic of COVID-19 mandates and lockdowns, to lead the National Institutes of Health (NIH). Bhattacharya, a professor of medicine and economics at Stanford University, has consistently voiced his opposition to pandemic restrictions, arguing that they have caused more harm than good. His appointment has drawn mixed reactions, with some praising his expertise and others expressing concern about his views on public health. The NIH is the leading medical research agency in the United States, responsible for funding and conducting research on a wide range of diseases and conditions. Bhattacharya's nomination must be confirmed by the Senate before he can officially take office.

name: DB Cooper
summary: The infamous D.B. Cooper case, a decades-old unsolved mystery concerning a plane hijacking in 1971, may be approaching a resolution. Recent discoveries have sparked renewed interest in the case, including the unearthing of a hidden parachute in the FBI's possession believed to be connected to the hijacker. This new evidence, along with advancements in forensic technology, could potentially lead to the identification of D.B. Cooper, whose true identity remains a closely guarded secret. The reopening of the case by the FBI and the emergence of crucial clues have raised hopes that this enigmatic mystery may finally be solved.

Additionally, American Airlines is working with Monumental Sports & Entertainment to unveil new United Globe Clubs and Lounges. However, Charlotte and Raleigh will not immediately receive the new "gate lice" technology. summary: In a thrilling showdown in Las Vegas, No. 1 Kansas emerged victorious over No. 11 Duke, securing the Jayhawks' second ranked win of the season. Despite a valiant effort from Duke, Kansas held on for a narrow 75-72 victory. In a separate road game, No. 12 Duke dominated No. 17 Arizona, securing a decisive 69-55 win. The victory marked Duke's continued success and its ability to stifle the Wildcats. While the Blue Devils' matchup against Kansas proved to be a close encounter, a series of unfortunate late-game spins ultimately proved costly for Duke. However, the Blue Devils remain confident in their abilities and are eager to continue their winning streak.

name: Walmart DEI policies
summary: Walmart, along with several other major corporations such as Toyota, has recently rolled back its diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) policies amidst conservative backlash. The move has sparked controversy, with some arguing that it is a step backward for diversity and inclusion in the workplace. Walmart's CEO, John Furner, has stated that the changes are intended to ensure that every customer feels welcome and included, regardless of their individual characteristics. The rollback of DEI policies has drawn both praise and criticism, with some praising it as a move towards neutrality and others criticizing it as a surrender to conservative pressure.
